# Project chooser config — read on the Windows side by autohotkey/projects.ahk.
# Copy to projects.txt (next to the .ahk scripts in Documents\autohotkey\) and edit.
# sync-ahk bootstraps it for you on first run, and never overwrites your edits.
#
# Paths point into the WSL filesystem over \\wsl$\<distro>\...
#   bare line   scan immediate subdirectories
#   =path       add this path directly
#   !pattern    ignore directories whose name matches
#   # comment

\\wsl$\Ubuntu\home\you\code
=\\wsl$\Ubuntu\home\you\dotfiles
!node_modules
